item.title: CVE-2019-12659|2024-09-16T20:42:03.657Z -- cisco -- cisco%20ios%20xe%20software%203.2.0ja
item.description: A vulnerability in the HTTP server code of Cisco IOS XE Software could allow an unauthenticated, remote attacker to cause the HTTP server to crash. The vulnerability is due to a logical error in the logging mechanism. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by generating a high amount of long-lived connections to the HTTP service on the device. A successful exploit could allow the attacker to cause the HTTP server to crash.
